<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0124 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book presents a normative end-use orientated approach to the energyproblem as an alternative to the conventional approach with its orientationtowards increased energy use. With this alternative approach, the focusof analysis shifts from the expansion of energy supplies to the waysin which energy is used and to the exploration of more effective waysof directing energy resources to human needs. The book covers the followingtopics: an end-use orientated energy strategy for industrialized countries;energy strategies for developing countries; global energy demand andsupply; policies for implementing energy strategies for a sustainableworld; the political economy of end-use energy strategies. Two extensiveappendices cover renewable energy resources and statistical data on worldenergy use.</TEXT></DOC>